        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-08-20 13:31:17.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n2 suggestions to improve the code quality :\n\n1)create a class \"E2eServiceUtils\" with static method :\n\n    public static boolean isE2EService(ServiceOrderItemInfo serviceOrderItemInfo){\n        Map<String,Object> sdcInfos = serviceOrderItemInfo.getCatalogResponse();\n        boolean e2eService = false;\n        if(sdcInfos.get(\"category\")!=null){\n            String category = ((String)sdcInfos.get(\"category\")).toLowerCase();\n            // Until SO comes up with one consolidated API for Service CRUD, ExtAPI has to be handle SO (serviceInstance and e2eServiceInstances )APIs for service CRUD\n            // All E2E Services are required to be created in SDC under category \"E2E Services\" until SO fixes the multiple API issue.\n            if(category.startsWith(\"e2e\")) {\n                e2eService = true;\n            }\n        }\n        return e2eService;\n    }\n\t\n\twhich is called in CheckOrderConsistenceManager and SOTaskProcessor\n\t\t-CheckOrderConsistenceManager line 104 to 111 replaced by :  boolean e2eService= E2eServiceUtils.isE2EService(serviceOrderItemInfo);\n\t\t-SOTaskProcessor line 84 to 91 replaced by : boolean e2eService = E2eServiceUtils.isE2EService(serviceOrderInfo.getServiceOrderItemInfos().get(serviceOrderItem.getId()));\n\n-> the same code is called to know if the item is an E2EService, and in the \"isE2EService\" method, we check if sdcInfos.get(\"category\") is not null.\n\n\n\n2)in CheckOrderConsistenceManager line 128 change\n (!serviceOrderConsumerService.isTenantIdPresentInAAI(serviceOrder) && !e2eService) by (!e2eService && !serviceOrderConsumerService.isTenantIdPresentInAAI(serviceOrder))\n \n -> we don't call aai to check the tenant if no need (case e2eService)",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
